race.comment: Competitive. RUSSIANTOTHEPOST (9) ran a nice race here on debut and then delivered her Maiden in good style at Ipswich. She looks as if she'll handle the mile comfortably and fitter again she looks capable of taking the next step. PARISIENNE PIPER (8) also won second-up delivering her Maiden here over this distance from the front. Was heavily bet and keeps the handy 2kg claim. On that effort she can win again without surprise. POUTCHEK (5) is third-up and much better placed this evening. Hasn't won for a long while but looks to be heading in the right direction, and Ben Thompson's booking is a decent push. BRUTAL BOWLER (1) is hard fit now and has to be kept onside. His effort here 12 days ago rates well enough. LADY WINDERMERE (7) got too far back at the Gold Coast but missed 1L here prior over 1300m. Is up to the mile for the first time and should be around the mark.
